STATE of North Carolina
v.
Kenneth E. ROBINSON. No. 200P07-2. Supreme Court of North Carolina. September 20, 2007. Kenneth E. Robinson, pro se. Kathleen U. Baldwin, Assistant Attorney General, William Graham, District Attorney, for State of NC. Grady Balentine, Assistant Attorney General, for COA Judges.

ORDER

Upon consideration of the application filed by Defendant on the 23rd day of August 2007 in this matter for Writ of Habeas Corpus, the following order was entered and is hereby certified to the Superior Court, Halifax County:

"Denied by order of the Court in conference, this the 20th day of September 2007."
